A definition file is either an Interface Definition file (*.idl) or a type library file (*.tlb). A type library can be linked into a component (*.ocx, *.dll, *.exe, ...)
A marshaller DLL can be generated from an IDL file. If generated, the marshaller DLL will automatically be registered by the Wizard.
A COM component can either be out-of-process (i.e. an executable that runs in a separate process) or in-process (i.e. a DLL that is loaded in the client process). Is the COM component:

The Wizard can delete all files in the destination folder before generating new files. Alternatively, it can backup files it overwrites or just overwrite them with no backup.
